[{"location":"lib/hilbert/#Hilbert-Space","page":"Hilbert Space","title":"Hilbert Space","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/hilbert/#API","page":"Hilbert Space","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/hilbert/","page":"Hilbert Space","title":"Hilbert Space","text":"Modules = [Atom.Hilbert]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/hilbert/#Atom.Hilbert.BinaryFock","page":"Hilbert Space","title":"Atom.Hilbert.BinaryFock","text":"Fock Basis for fermion and hard-core boson, each site has two states with occupation number 0 and 1 e.g. |101>↓|100>↑ means a 3-site fock state, site 1: one up one down, site 2: no particle, site 3: one down \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"lib/green/#Many-body-Green's-Functions","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Many-body Green's Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/green/#API","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/green/","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Many-body Green's Functions","text":"Modules = [Atom.Green]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/green/#Atom.Green.GreenN","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Atom.Green.GreenN","text":"GreenN(m::Model, τ, orbital, isfermi=true)\n\nConstruct struct to store the variables to evaulate N-body Green's functions. The leg index is assumed to be [1, 2, 3, ...,2N], where the incoming legs are 1:N, and the outgoing legs are N+1:2N The full Green's function is defined as,\n\nG_2N=leftmathcalT c_2Nc_2N-1c_N+1c^+_Nc^+_2c^+_1right\n\ne.g.,\n\n1->------->-3\n    | G4 |        \n2->------->-4\n\nAll other Green's function are derived from the above full Green's function\n\n#Arguments\n\nm: Model struct\nτ: array stores the imaginary-time of legs\norbital: array stores the orbital/spin of legs\nN: particle number (Note that the leg numebr is 2N)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"lib/green/#Atom.Green.Model","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Atom.Green.Model","text":"Model(H::Operator, c⁺::Vector{Operator}, c⁻::Vector{Operator})\n\nConstruct a model.  All input operators are in the Fock space. But all members of Model struct is in the eigenspace. Operator should be a matrix type.\n\nArguments:\n\nβ: inverse temperature\nH: Hamiltonian in the Fock space\nc⁺, c⁻: creation/anniliation operators for each orbital, all in the Fock space\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"lib/green/#Atom.Green.Gn-Tuple{Atom.Green.Model, Atom.Green.GreenN}","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Atom.Green.Gn","text":"@inline function Gn(m::Model, g::GreenN)\n\nEvaluate the full N-body Green's function.\n\nG_2N=leftmathcalT c_2Nc_2N-1c_N+1c^+_Nc^+_2c^+_1right\n\ne.g.,\n\n1->------->-3\n    | G4 |        \n2->------->-4\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"lib/green/#Atom.Green.Gnc-Tuple{Atom.Green.Model, Atom.Green.GreenN}","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Atom.Green.Gnc","text":"function Gnc(m::Model, g::GreenN)\n\nEvaluate the connected N-body Green's function.\n\ne.g., G4c(43;21) =     1->–––->-4       1->–––->-4     1->–-   –->-4         | G4 |      -                  +         X        2->–––->-3       2->–––->-3     2->–-   –->-3\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"lib/green/#Atom.Green.Heisenberg-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Any, Any}","page":"Many-body Green's Functions","title":"Atom.Green.Heisenberg","text":"Heisenberg(o::Operator, E, τ)\n\nTransform operator o into Heisenberg picture\n\n    exp(Hτ)cdot o cdot exp(-Hτ)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Atom","category":"page"},{"location":"#Atom","page":"Home","title":"Atom","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for Atom.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [Atom]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Library-Outline","page":"Home","title":"Library Outline","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\n    \"lib/green.md\",\n    \"lib/hubbard.md\",\n    \"lib/hilbert.md\",\n]\nDepth = 2","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/hubbard/#Exact-Diagonalization-of-Hubbard-Model","page":"Exact Diagonalization of Hubbard Model","title":"Exact Diagonalization of Hubbard Model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/hubbard/#API","page":"Exact Diagonalization of Hubbard Model","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/hubbard/","page":"Exact Diagonalization of Hubbard Model","title":"Exact Diagonalization of Hubbard Model","text":"Modules = [Atom.Hubbard]","category":"page"}]
